Encode Sans Expanded Thin Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded Thin'.

Pass

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansExpanded-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Expanded ExtraLight Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansExpanded-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Expanded ExtraLight Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded ExtraLight'.

Encode Sans Expanded Light Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded Light'.

Pass

Encode Sans Expanded Medium Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansExpanded-Medium', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Expanded Medium Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded Medium'.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded SemiBold'.

Encode Sans Expanded Bold (EncodeSansExpanded-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansExpanded-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

but what do think about this
'Encode Sans is a trademark of Fontsmith Ltd and may be registered in certain jurisdictions.'

License text

Cannot check license text because of unkown entity 'Impallari Type' (NID8). Please verify against job spec.
MS NID 13 is:
This Font Software is licensed under the SIL Open Font License, Version 1.1. This license is available with a FAQ at: http://scripts.sil.org/OFL
, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Encode Sans Expanded ExtraBold Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded ExtraBold'.

Pass

Encode Sans Expanded Black Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Black.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansExpanded-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Expanded Black Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansExpanded-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Expanded Black Regular (EncodeSansExpanded-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Expanded' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Expanded Black'.

Pass
